        "FACS Lecturer Pool",
        "Submission Requirements"
      ],
      "contentBlocks": [
        "The Department of Family and Consumer Sciences continuously accepts applicants to our temporary lecturer pool. A Master\u2019s degree in the subject area or specialized post-secondary certification is normally the minimum requirement depending on the program, although a doctorate or equivalent is often preferred. Teaching experience in the subject area is generally highly desired and may be required.",
        "In order to be considered for a part-time lecturer position please submit an application to the CSUS Recruitment Portal - Page Up.",
        "You will be asked to provide the following:",
        "Courses Qualified to Teach: FACS Department Form",
        "Statement of Professional Preparation and Experience Form",
        "Optional: Letters of recommendation or any other supporting documents you prefer"
      ],
