        "Connect with Family Studies & Human Development",
        "Find Us",
        "Contact Us",
        "Meet Us"
      ],
      "contentBlocks": [
        "The Family Studies & Human Development (FSHD) program at Sac State has experienced a growth rate of 150% over the past five years.",
        "The major prepares students for careers in various human service fields. The program emphasizes an asset-based approach to understanding lifespan human development, family systems, and family diversity in a cultural context.",
        "The major is approved by the National Council on Family Relations (NCFR) for academic programs in Family Life Education.",
        "Family Studies & Human Development Advising Sheet",
        "Sacramento State College Corps: paid, off-campus",
        "For additional information on career opportunities visit We Are Family Science",
